1
00:00:09,400 --> 00:00:14,280
(This program is intended for mature audiences.
It may feature explicit content, violence, and strong language)

2
00:00:14,280 --> 00:00:20,040
(All characters, places, and events
in this series are entirely fictitious)

3
00:00:20,080 --> 00:00:20,920
Ouch!

4
00:00:22,240 --> 00:00:23,520
Ouch, it hurts!

5
00:00:23,520 --> 00:00:24,720
- Ouch!
- Hmm.

6
00:00:25,520 --> 00:00:28,200
- Ouch, enough!
- Not done yet.

7
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:32,440
Ouch, it hurts! Ouch, it hurts! Ouch!

8
00:00:39,920 --> 00:00:40,680
Oh!

9
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:47,440
You're still sulking over Ice?

10
00:00:49,080 --> 00:00:52,200
He didn't cross any lines.
He didn't touch me. He wasn't handsy

11
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:53,840
or anything at all.

12
00:00:55,760 --> 00:00:58,640
Honestly, Krit, he's actually
a good customer of mine.

13
00:01:01,160 --> 00:01:02,880
So that's why you had to be
so sweet to him, huh?

14
00:01:04,720 --> 00:01:09,280
I'm investigating the case for you,
so I have to blend in.

15
00:01:09,440 --> 00:01:12,600
Who am I? I'm Wayu, the top detective.

16
00:01:20,120 --> 00:01:21,000
Krit.

17
00:01:23,320 --> 00:01:24,200
I think...

18
00:01:25,240 --> 00:01:27,440
Would it be a good idea
if I left Moonlit?

19
00:01:32,880 --> 00:01:36,200
Do you really mean it, or are you
just trying to make it up to me?

20
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:53,560
The case is about to be resolved,

21
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:57,280
so there's no need for me to be a host.

22
00:02:00,960 --> 00:02:04,680
Didn't you say you like your friends
and the workplace?

23
00:02:05,680 --> 00:02:07,080
Yes, I do.

24
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:12,560
But I don't want others to look at you
strangely, and...

25
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:16,400
I don't want you to worry about this.

26
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:33,040
There's plenty of time to think
about this before the case ends.

27
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:36,960
Let's bring down big boss Por first.

28
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:39,240
Then we can talk
about you quitting later.

29
00:02:40,480 --> 00:02:41,600
Yes, sir.

30
00:02:41,880 --> 00:02:42,960
If I can catch him, that is.

31
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,920
Of course you will. You'll get him.

32
00:02:46,920 --> 00:02:51,040
Because you're a police officer
who truly serves the people.

33
00:02:51,920 --> 00:02:53,640
But even if you don't...

34
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:59,000
I'm still proud of you.

35
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:02,120
- Mm.
- Ouch.

36
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:04,400
- What's wrong?
- It hurts.

37
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:09,520
- Sorry. Come here, let me fix it.
- No, it's fine.

38
00:03:17,720 --> 00:03:20,280
(Come home right now.)

39
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:37,960
=Love of Silom=

40
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:50,560
Calm down. Let him explain first.

41
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:57,080
Krit, this was the plan, wasn't it?

42
00:03:57,440 --> 00:03:59,800
Tell him it was part of the plan.

43
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:08,400
You aren't misunderstanding anything.

44
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:11,240
And this isn't part of any plan.

45
00:04:12,840 --> 00:04:15,520
The man I kissed is my boyfriend.

46
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:19,120
I planned to introduce him to Mom
and Dad after the case was over.

47
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:21,680
Properly, so you could get to know him.

48
00:04:21,920 --> 00:04:24,120
What kind of crazy nonsense is that?

49
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:28,880
What are you doing with your life?
Are you trying to ruin everything?

50
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:32,000
You just can't be normal, can you?

51
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,640
I've always been normal.

52
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:36,640
It's only in your eyes

53
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:39,760
- that I'm not normal like others.
- What about Rose?

54
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:42,840
How will you explain this to her?

55
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:45,520
She has known from the start.

56
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:49,600
We were never really
going to get married.

57
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:52,800
We only did it to put Dad at ease.

58
00:04:53,920 --> 00:04:56,400
You can call Rose's parents
over right now.

59
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:57,600
Set the wedding date soon.

60
00:04:57,600 --> 00:05:00,080
- Tell them not to worry about the dowry...
- No.

61
00:05:02,240 --> 00:05:06,160
I'm not marrying Rose.
Rose and I are just friends.

62
00:05:09,120 --> 00:05:10,400
I like men.

63
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:15,040
I've done everything you wanted, Dad.
I studied hard to be a cop.

64
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:19,720
To prove myself
and follow in your footsteps.

65
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:26,240
But this is one thing I can't change.
I was born this way.

66
00:05:29,280 --> 00:05:32,120
I didn't raise you to be abnormal.

67
00:05:32,720 --> 00:05:36,000
And your mother never raised you
to think this way either.

68
00:05:42,440 --> 00:05:46,800
But this is who I am.
Can't you accept me, Dad?

69
00:05:47,960 --> 00:05:51,720
Honey, please stop. I'm begging you.
Let's talk about this another day.

70
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:55,280
Go break up with him now.

71
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:58,840
If you won't, I'll handle it myself.

72
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:02,800
You know I can do
more than you think, Krit.

73
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:04,240
Remember that.

74
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:13,360
Krit.

75
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:17,520
Dad expects a lot from you.

76
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:21,920
Please try to understand him.

77
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:09,760
(Incoming call)

78
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:03,440
(Come to the gym with Tai.)

79
00:08:03,760 --> 00:08:07,480
(So what happened at home?
You just vanished.)

80
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:14,080
Did you and the captain fight again?

81
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:16,280
No.

82
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:20,880
He just said he had
something urgent at home.

83
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:23,200
After that, I couldn't reach him at all.

84
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:25,280
Sigh.

85
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:29,960
Don't overthink it. It might be nothing.

86
00:08:29,960 --> 00:08:32,800
He might just be tired or busy.

87
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:35,360
He is a cop, okay? Not a bar host.

88
00:08:35,640 --> 00:08:38,360
His job's probably way harder than ours.

89
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:41,800
Really?

90
00:08:43,040 --> 00:08:47,560
But I've got a feeling that
this time is different from the usual.

91
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:54,840
Can you have a little faith in your super
handsome, steak-devouring boyfriend? Huh?

92
00:08:55,720 --> 00:08:59,040
If something was wrong,
he'd have called you by now.

93
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:00,720
- Right?
- Sigh.

94
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:02,800
Hey, get what I'm saying?

95
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:05,000
Come here. Don't be sad.

96
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:07,200
Come on, work out with me.

97
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:09,960
Turn that sadness into energy, buddy.

98
00:09:18,560 --> 00:09:21,440
Wayu, you seem miles away.
Come on, get up.

99
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:23,400
Oh, sorry.

100
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:29,000
Your boyfriend didn't come today?
I wanted a photo with him. He's famous.

101
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:31,480
Is something wrong between you two?

102
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:34,360
- Nothing. He's just busy, that's all.
- Here.

103
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:38,040
Look at this, "Hot cop,
tell your friends."

104
00:09:38,040 --> 00:09:42,640
The girls here are all screaming for him.
You can't let your guard down.

105
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:48,560
Good job, good future.
Someone might snatch him up.

106
00:09:48,560 --> 00:09:51,120
- Snatch him up.
- Sis!

107
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:53,160
Well, the customer is calling.
The customer is calling.

108
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:55,280
The customer will leave. Hurry up.

109
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:58,920
- The customer's leaving.
- Way to kill the mood.

110
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:13,440
(I'm sleeping at HQ tonight.
I won't be back at the condo)

111
00:10:13,560 --> 00:10:15,800
(Wayu: Is everything okay?
Did something happen?)

112
00:10:15,920 --> 00:10:17,800
(Krit: Nothing at all)

113
00:10:24,680 --> 00:10:25,600
Hmm.

114
00:10:27,640 --> 00:10:32,240
See? The captain texted you back.
Told you, you're overthinking.

115
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:36,240
But my gut says something's off.

116
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:41,800
Think about it.
He said he'd sleep at HQ.

117
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:44,920
When he usually comes home,
no matter how late it is.

118
00:10:45,440 --> 00:10:46,360
What do you think?

119
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:52,520
You said it yourself, didn't you?
He's about to wrap up the case.

120
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:54,840
He's probably just busy.

121
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:57,800
Yeah, maybe.

122
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:04,840
Hmm, I think you worry
too much about him.

123
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:09,400
Worry about yourself instead.
Have you told Foei about your quitting?

124
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:12,000
Sigh.

125
00:11:12,760 --> 00:11:16,880
Either way, I should wait till
Por's case is over.

126
00:11:17,280 --> 00:11:20,600
Then I'll finally work up the nerve
to tell Foei I'm quitting.

127
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:23,040
So Foei has time to get ready.

128
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:29,720
But you've really
thought it through, huh? About quitting?

129
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:32,720
You're not doing this just
because of the captain, are you?

130
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:34,760
No, that's not it.

131
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:39,640
Honestly, Krit just made me think
about my own future.

132
00:11:39,640 --> 00:11:41,880
About what I want for myself.

133
00:11:42,840 --> 00:11:43,680
And...

134
00:11:45,160 --> 00:11:46,800
I like being a host.

135
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:50,760
I like my friends here.

136
00:11:53,160 --> 00:11:56,080
- But I want to go back to study and graduate.
- Hmm.

137
00:11:57,040 --> 00:12:01,240
I know. Being an architect
is your dream.

138
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:06,040
Then go make it happen.

139
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:11,280
When you quit,
come visit if you miss us.

140
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:12,840
Got it?

141
00:12:17,920 --> 00:12:19,880
- Thank you, buddy.
- Mm.

142
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:22,960
Also, thank you
for all this time together.

143
00:12:24,360 --> 00:12:25,440
I feel a sudden emptiness.

144
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:33,080
Staying quiet like this

145
00:12:34,080 --> 00:12:36,200
means you want to end up
in prison like Chain?

146
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:41,240
You know who was behind Chain's death.

147
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:45,720
Who else? The police.

148
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:51,680
The police are supposed
to protect people and uphold the law.

149
00:12:53,720 --> 00:12:56,440
I was ordered to protect Chain.

150
00:12:56,440 --> 00:12:58,960
Because Chain was a key witness
in the case.

151
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:03,400
But in the end, he was killed in prison.

152
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:08,520
You can guess who was behind it, right?

153
00:13:11,680 --> 00:13:13,640
- I don't know.
- But I do.

154
00:13:14,560 --> 00:13:17,000
For someone who's ready
to cover up their own crime,

155
00:13:17,680 --> 00:13:21,000
one corpse or two,
it doesn't make any difference.

156
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:24,520
Captain, report coming in. We got Por.

157
00:13:24,520 --> 00:13:26,840
He was caught trying
to flee near the border.

158
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:32,560
Your backup has been arrested.

159
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:36,000
All your money trails
are being investigated.

160
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:39,920
If you confess now,
I can still help you.

161
00:13:40,440 --> 00:13:43,360
If not, you're going to prison.

162
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:47,640
Then we'll see if you can escape
your boss's reach.

163
00:13:47,640 --> 00:13:48,640
Hey, wait.

164
00:13:48,640 --> 00:13:51,400
I only sent the boys and girls
Por asked for.

165
00:13:52,280 --> 00:13:55,880
How would I know what happened
after that? That's all I did.

166
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:59,560
So you're saying
you knew nothing at all?

167
00:14:00,280 --> 00:14:03,080
- Where those people ended up.
- Yeah, I didn't know.

168
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:06,200
I just brought the boys and girls
to meet Chain.

169
00:14:06,640 --> 00:14:11,320
After that, they were sent overseas
to entertain guests for Por.

170
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:13,040
I didn't know about it anymore.

171
00:14:13,560 --> 00:14:16,800
So you're saying you had no idea that
you were part of a human trafficking ring?

172
00:14:22,880 --> 00:14:25,320
Your information isn't
important anymore.

173
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:27,120
I'll get what I need from Por myself.

174
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:31,840
- Lock him up. Tell the warden to watch him.
- Wait. I have information.

175
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:34,400
Por isn't anywhere near the top
of the human trafficking trade.

176
00:14:35,680 --> 00:14:38,120
I heard he received orders from someone.

177
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:41,760
They said if anyone's disobedient,
they would sell their organs.

178
00:14:43,040 --> 00:14:44,520
That's all I know.

179
00:14:55,720 --> 00:14:56,760
Oh.

180
00:14:59,960 --> 00:15:01,000
Oh.

181
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:06,800
Singto.

182
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:15,840
What are you drawing, dear?

183
00:15:19,880 --> 00:15:22,920
Oh, sigh.

184
00:15:32,320 --> 00:15:34,360
I'm not sure what's up with Papa, right?

185
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:51,000
Hello.

186
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:54,520
Yes, it's my mom.

187
00:15:56,920 --> 00:15:58,680
Okay, I'll rush over.

188
00:16:00,280 --> 00:16:01,520
(Visiting hours for detainees:
8 AM to 9 AM)

189
00:16:01,520 --> 00:16:02,680
(12 PM to 1 PM, 4 PM to 5 PM)

190
00:16:02,680 --> 00:16:04,720
(All visitor items
must be inspected by supervisor)

191
00:16:10,840 --> 00:16:13,080
Honestly, how old are you, Mom?

192
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:15,320
Do we have to keep watching you
the whole time?

193
00:16:15,320 --> 00:16:18,480
Hmm, they didn't ask you
to come here and complain.

194
00:16:18,640 --> 00:16:22,000
The police called you to bail me out,
not to lecture.

195
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:24,600
Because you never learn, Mom.
I have to teach you, right?

196
00:16:24,680 --> 00:16:26,920
Hey, Wai, I'm your mom.

197
00:16:27,680 --> 00:16:30,240
Do you want other people
to think you're ungrateful or what?

198
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:33,880
You abandoned your own child,
and you've still got the nerve to scold me?

199
00:16:35,120 --> 00:16:37,080
Well, I've changed myself, okay?

200
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:41,040
Unlike you, you keep causing trouble.

201
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:45,400
When are you going to quit
gambling and buying lottery tickets?

202
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:47,960
A debt of over a hundred thousand?
Who's supposed to pay that off?

203
00:16:47,960 --> 00:16:51,520
Are you going to make Wayu
clean up after you till he dies?

204
00:16:51,520 --> 00:16:54,000
- I earned money for you, didn't I?
- Ow!

205
00:16:55,080 --> 00:16:56,080
Wai, come here.

206
00:16:58,040 --> 00:17:01,320
Singto, stay with Mom for now.
I will be right behind you.

207
00:17:01,320 --> 00:17:02,440
I'll be right there.

208
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:07,320
Wayu, did you sort out the bail yet?

209
00:17:07,320 --> 00:17:09,560
Did the police say I can leave now?

210
00:17:10,240 --> 00:17:12,600
No, Mom. I don't have the money.

211
00:17:12,760 --> 00:17:16,160
Then go get some.

212
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:18,920
Just take the money
from Wai's fund first.

213
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:22,080
Well, that ungrateful type needs to pay
back her debt of gratitude to me anyway.

214
00:17:25,520 --> 00:17:28,560
Mom, money doesn't just
fall from the sky.

215
00:17:29,400 --> 00:17:33,040
Do you even know what Wai
and I go through? Huh?

216
00:17:33,640 --> 00:17:35,920
Wai is starving herself
of sleep packing stuff,

217
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:38,120
just so you can work with her!

218
00:17:39,880 --> 00:17:43,480
And do you know why I had to drop out?
Why I can't have a life like other kids?

219
00:17:45,080 --> 00:17:46,920
It's because I have to be a host,

220
00:17:46,920 --> 00:17:49,840
working alone to pay off
your debts, not Singto's.

221
00:17:50,120 --> 00:17:54,160
It'll be over soon.
Then you can go back to school.

222
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:55,320
Huh?

223
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:59,560
How can it ever end
when you never stop, Mom?

224
00:18:01,120 --> 00:18:02,760
I'm already exhausted, Mom.

225
00:18:06,960 --> 00:18:10,720
Go borrow from people at work
or your friends. One last time.

226
00:18:10,720 --> 00:18:12,280
Just this once, I promise.

227
00:18:12,280 --> 00:18:15,480
I swear I'll quit after this.
Quit for real.

228
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:17,360
You say that every time though.

229
00:18:18,440 --> 00:18:20,840
But this is the first time I'm choosing
to trust myself.

230
00:18:22,720 --> 00:18:25,240
But I promised, Wayu.

231
00:18:34,640 --> 00:18:36,360
(Go break up with him now.)

232
00:18:36,760 --> 00:18:39,400
(If you won't, I'll handle it myself.)

233
00:18:39,920 --> 00:18:43,360
(You know I can do
more than you think, Krit.)

234
00:18:43,840 --> 00:18:46,280
Por still hasn't said a word.

235
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:51,920
I think it'll be hard this time
to reach the real mastermind.

236
00:18:54,840 --> 00:18:55,720
Lieutenant.

237
00:18:56,360 --> 00:18:59,760
Call the team together.
I need to plan the next move.

238
00:18:59,760 --> 00:19:00,920
Yes, Captain.

239
00:19:09,520 --> 00:19:12,520
(Krit, are you at the station?)

240
00:19:20,720 --> 00:19:24,240
(Not right now. I'm out on a case)

241
00:19:31,640 --> 00:19:33,240
Is something wrong, Captain?

242
00:19:34,320 --> 00:19:37,600
Oh, it's nothing, Inspector.

243
00:19:46,360 --> 00:19:48,280
Has everyone been told to wait
in the meeting room?

244
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:50,200
- Yes.
- Okay.

245
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:05,360
Then I'll head to the meeting room
and wait there first.

246
00:20:06,160 --> 00:20:09,160
Just hurry and come. We need to talk.

247
00:20:09,760 --> 00:20:10,760
Yes, sir.

248
00:20:19,320 --> 00:20:21,720
Didn't you say you weren't
at the station?

249
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:23,560
Well...

250
00:20:25,240 --> 00:20:27,040
Why would you lie to me?

251
00:20:29,040 --> 00:20:32,000
Did I do something wrong?

252
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:40,680
Sorry.

253
00:20:42,480 --> 00:20:46,600
You should go home first.
We'll talk later.

254
00:20:50,520 --> 00:20:51,520
Okay.

255
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:06,880
Then whenever you're free
and want to see me,

256
00:21:07,320 --> 00:21:08,640
just let me know.

257
00:21:26,720 --> 00:21:28,120
Take care of yourself.

258
00:21:51,880 --> 00:21:53,280
Good. You're here.

259
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:55,720
I've already picked an auspicious date
for you and Rose.

260
00:21:56,680 --> 00:22:00,320
Once you close the trafficking case,
clear your schedule.

261
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:05,120
I thought I made myself clear.
There won't be a wedding.

262
00:22:05,120 --> 00:22:07,080
You should ask Rose too.

263
00:22:08,280 --> 00:22:11,880
She isn't a cop, and she's not
your subordinate.

264
00:22:12,360 --> 00:22:14,720
You can't make decisions
for other people like this.

265
00:22:15,440 --> 00:22:17,760
If she isn't okay, then change.

266
00:22:18,240 --> 00:22:20,440
There are plenty of other well-profiled
women for you to choose from.

267
00:22:20,440 --> 00:22:22,880
Even my friend's daughter,
it's not difficult at all.

268
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:26,560
Krit has his reasons. Give it some time.

269
00:22:27,280 --> 00:22:30,200
I don't see why we need to rush so much.

270
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:33,160
Keep quiet, that's how he gets spoiled.

271
00:22:33,840 --> 00:22:36,120
Raise him to be weak,
and this is what happens.

272
00:22:36,880 --> 00:22:38,880
And do you have to go this far?

273
00:22:39,920 --> 00:22:41,720
You can see he feels uncomfortable.

274
00:22:44,480 --> 00:22:48,120
You care about him, but do you care
about me too?

275
00:22:48,760 --> 00:22:52,320
If Krit marries a man, how am I
supposed to answer the media and others?

276
00:22:52,720 --> 00:22:54,920
Do you want me to be
a laughingstock in the community?

277
00:22:55,440 --> 00:22:57,400
Krit! Come back first.

278
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:24,600
(Mobile 1 Thai)

279
00:24:11,960 --> 00:24:13,080
(There you are.)

280
00:24:29,160 --> 00:24:35,520
♪Only after we parted did I know♪

281
00:24:35,520 --> 00:24:43,480
♪Life was so much brighter
with you here♪

282
00:24:43,480 --> 00:24:52,120
♪Now I truly know what loneliness means♪

283
00:24:52,120 --> 00:24:58,200
♪When we're far apart♪

284
00:24:58,200 --> 00:25:03,000
♪I finally reflect♪

285
00:25:03,440 --> 00:25:06,200
♪That it was me♪

286
00:25:06,200 --> 00:25:11,280
♪Who chose the wrong path♪

287
00:25:11,480 --> 00:25:16,520
♪One that breaks my own heart♪

288
00:25:16,880 --> 00:25:20,640
♪Honestly, I never wanted to leave you♪

289
00:25:20,640 --> 00:25:23,560
♪I never wanted to be this far away♪

290
00:25:23,560 --> 00:25:26,000
♪But I accidentally did something♪

291
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:31,400
(Left with Only Memories by Indigo)
♪Said things in spite, so wrong♪

292
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:34,160
♪Shedding tears♪

293
00:25:34,160 --> 00:25:39,880
♪Over the words of my own♪

294
00:25:48,600 --> 00:25:52,080
Let me introduce you all to DJ Wayu.

295
00:25:54,280 --> 00:25:56,400
Let me hear some noise
from the left side!

296
00:25:57,800 --> 00:26:00,000
Don't give in, right side.
Let me hear some noise!

297
00:26:02,960 --> 00:26:04,800
Please welcome Kenji!

298
00:26:07,800 --> 00:26:08,760
Here comes Richy.

299
00:26:34,560 --> 00:26:35,960
(Wai)
(I went to bail Mom out.)

300
00:26:36,360 --> 00:26:37,360
(I can't take it anymore.)

301
00:26:41,640 --> 00:26:42,200
Wayu.

302
00:26:42,760 --> 00:26:43,360
Wayu.

303
00:26:43,600 --> 00:26:44,160
Hmm?

304
00:26:44,720 --> 00:26:46,520
What a coincidence.
I just ran into some friends too.

305
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:48,080
- Oh, really?
- Mmm.

306
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:50,080
Should we ask them to join our table?
Might make things more fun.

307
00:26:50,440 --> 00:26:51,080
No, I don't want to.

308
00:26:51,560 --> 00:26:53,720
I've already booked Wayu.
I'm not sharing you with anyone.

309
00:26:54,200 --> 00:26:54,760
Hmm.

310
00:26:54,920 --> 00:26:55,640
Sure.

311
00:26:56,400 --> 00:26:57,720
You know?

312
00:26:57,720 --> 00:27:00,360
Actually, for the whole night,
just 40 drinks are enough.

313
00:27:00,720 --> 00:27:02,680
You don't need to book 100 drinks
like every night.

314
00:27:03,240 --> 00:27:04,240
No way.

315
00:27:04,720 --> 00:27:05,600
It'll ruin my reputation.

316
00:27:06,160 --> 00:27:07,400
To book the number one host,

317
00:27:07,800 --> 00:27:09,000
it's a 100-drink minimum, you know?

318
00:27:09,800 --> 00:27:11,600
Plus, I'm just too jealous
to let anyone else have you.

319
00:27:12,240 --> 00:27:12,800
Hmm.

320
00:27:13,160 --> 00:27:13,840
Alright.

321
00:27:15,760 --> 00:27:17,280
So, what do you want to do today?

322
00:27:18,440 --> 00:27:19,400
Hmm.

323
00:27:19,800 --> 00:27:20,600
Don't worry about me at all.

324
00:27:21,280 --> 00:27:22,160
Better focus on yourself.

325
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:24,280
Whatever you want to do today,
let's do that.

326
00:27:25,960 --> 00:27:26,880
How's that, Mind?

327
00:27:26,880 --> 00:27:27,440
Whoops.

328
00:27:27,440 --> 00:27:29,760
You are the customer.
I have to cater to you, Mind.

329
00:27:30,760 --> 00:27:31,520
So how about this?

330
00:27:32,520 --> 00:27:33,920
As a customer, my request is

331
00:27:34,840 --> 00:27:36,000
that let me entertain you a bit, Wayu.

332
00:27:40,160 --> 00:27:40,720
But...

333
00:27:42,120 --> 00:27:43,360
I don't have anything I want to do.

334
00:27:44,680 --> 00:27:45,280
Then...

335
00:27:46,400 --> 00:27:46,960
How about dancing?

336
00:27:47,440 --> 00:27:48,200
Dance with me for a bit.

337
00:27:49,280 --> 00:27:50,400
Let's dance right here.

338
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:53,040
Let's dance. Just dance.

339
00:27:54,320 --> 00:27:54,960
Let's dance.

340
00:27:55,560 --> 00:27:56,880
Dance until you forget
whatever's on your mind.

341
00:28:02,280 --> 00:28:02,800
Hey.

342
00:28:03,880 --> 00:28:04,480
Is something wrong?

343
00:28:07,800 --> 00:28:08,920
You can't completely hide from me.

344
00:28:09,520 --> 00:28:10,880
Just one look in your eyes
and I can tell you're sad.

345
00:28:11,120 --> 00:28:11,720
Hmph.

346
00:28:12,680 --> 00:28:13,200
What's wrong?

347
00:28:14,120 --> 00:28:15,160
Did you have a fight
with your boyfriend?

348
00:28:17,960 --> 00:28:18,640
How did you know?

349
00:28:24,560 --> 00:28:25,120
Well...

350
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:27,040
I just feel like

351
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:29,080
things have changed.

352
00:28:31,720 --> 00:28:32,520
Sigh.

353
00:28:33,280 --> 00:28:35,160
You two were pretty heated that day.

354
00:28:37,240 --> 00:28:38,480
As your friend...

355
00:28:39,520 --> 00:28:41,080
If you're together,
you've got to talk things out.

356
00:28:42,400 --> 00:28:43,880
So you don't keep spiraling like this.

357
00:28:44,640 --> 00:28:45,440
If it's not working,

358
00:28:46,760 --> 00:28:47,640
just find someone new.

359
00:28:51,320 --> 00:28:53,160
Look at you, slipping in
while he's away.

360
00:28:56,360 --> 00:28:57,080
Come on. Don't stress.

361
00:28:57,760 --> 00:28:58,560
Let's go dance instead.

362
00:28:59,560 --> 00:29:00,320
Come dance.

363
00:29:01,720 --> 00:29:02,320
Hey.

364
00:29:02,320 --> 00:29:03,440
Whoa.

365
00:29:03,440 --> 00:29:04,400
Let's just have a drink instead.

366
00:29:04,480 --> 00:29:05,040
Cheers.

367
00:29:05,040 --> 00:29:06,040
Woo.

368
00:29:31,120 --> 00:29:33,280
Wayu's still working.

369
00:29:33,680 --> 00:29:34,960
Let's wait outside, Captain.

370
00:29:37,600 --> 00:29:39,400
Go ahead.

371
00:29:43,440 --> 00:29:44,040
Come here.

372
00:29:46,040 --> 00:29:46,560
Mmm.

373
00:29:49,000 --> 00:29:50,360
I'll get going now.

374
00:29:50,360 --> 00:29:51,480
Get home safe.

375
00:29:58,520 --> 00:29:59,280
Then I should head out too.

376
00:29:59,280 --> 00:30:00,280
Hey, wait.

377
00:30:02,400 --> 00:30:03,520
Did you two fight again?

378
00:30:07,760 --> 00:30:09,520
I don't mean to pry,

379
00:30:10,120 --> 00:30:11,320
but I don't want to be the third wheel.

380
00:30:13,040 --> 00:30:14,400
But I just feel so sorry for my friend.

381
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:17,400
Wayu's really serious about you,
Captain, you know.

382
00:30:17,720 --> 00:30:19,400
Serious enough to quit this job.

383
00:30:19,480 --> 00:30:20,480
All for you.

384
00:30:21,280 --> 00:30:22,920
With things this messy,

385
00:30:26,400 --> 00:30:29,040
isn't there anything you can do
to make it better, Captain?

386
00:30:56,480 --> 00:30:57,200
Uh-huh.

387
00:30:57,800 --> 00:30:59,000
Ahem.

388
00:30:59,480 --> 00:31:00,520
Are you okay, Mind?

389
00:31:01,120 --> 00:31:01,840
Ugh.

390
00:31:02,720 --> 00:31:04,240
Oh, take it easy.

391
00:31:05,120 --> 00:31:05,760
Oops.

392
00:31:05,760 --> 00:31:06,320
Urgh.

393
00:31:06,480 --> 00:31:07,240
- Haha.
- Ow.

394
00:31:07,360 --> 00:31:08,000
That's rough.

395
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:08,800
Ow.

396
00:31:09,200 --> 00:31:10,160
Just a moment.

397
00:31:10,160 --> 00:31:10,760
Still alright.

398
00:31:10,760 --> 00:31:11,360
Are you alright?

399
00:31:11,360 --> 00:31:11,920
Oh.

400
00:31:11,920 --> 00:31:12,920
Hang on.

401
00:31:13,320 --> 00:31:13,920
Sigh.

402
00:31:14,400 --> 00:31:15,160
Sigh.

403
00:31:16,360 --> 00:31:17,320
Sorry.

404
00:31:17,720 --> 00:31:18,280
Ouch.

405
00:31:18,280 --> 00:31:19,400
Ouch, no need to apologize.

406
00:31:19,400 --> 00:31:19,920
Sigh.

407
00:31:19,920 --> 00:31:21,320
It's my fault.

408
00:31:21,440 --> 00:31:22,880
I drank way too much.

409
00:31:23,160 --> 00:31:25,000
I haven't drunk
like I wanted in so long.

410
00:31:25,760 --> 00:31:27,600
It was a bit too fun.

411
00:31:28,200 --> 00:31:29,240
Ouch.

412
00:31:30,040 --> 00:31:30,880
Sigh.

413
00:31:32,320 --> 00:31:33,040
Hold on, Mind.

414
00:31:33,040 --> 00:31:33,560
Sigh.

415
00:31:48,040 --> 00:31:48,640
Hello.

416
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:50,040
Wayu.

417
00:31:51,080 --> 00:31:52,560
Come see me when you're done with work.

418
00:31:53,320 --> 00:31:54,000
Sure.

419
00:31:54,280 --> 00:31:55,160
At home, right?

420
00:31:55,480 --> 00:31:56,400
I'll be done soon.

421
00:32:00,520 --> 00:32:01,320
Let's meet at the park.

422
00:32:04,240 --> 00:32:06,280
Alright, see you at the park.

423
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:16,880
Sigh.

424
00:32:16,920 --> 00:32:17,640
Hurry up, Mind.

425
00:32:18,560 --> 00:32:19,520
Let's head home now, quickly.

426
00:32:19,520 --> 00:32:20,000
Hup.

427
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:22,080
Hey, keep going. It's still fun.

428
00:32:22,160 --> 00:32:23,000
That's enough.

429
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:23,560
Oh.

430
00:32:23,560 --> 00:32:24,360
Can you get up?

431
00:32:24,360 --> 00:32:25,520
Okay, one, two, three.

432
00:32:25,520 --> 00:32:26,560
Easy.

433
00:32:26,720 --> 00:32:28,040
Heave-ho. Ow.

434
00:32:28,520 --> 00:32:30,080
Easy. Hang on.

435
00:32:30,760 --> 00:32:31,760
Okay, up.

436
00:32:44,640 --> 00:32:45,160
Krit.

437
00:32:45,560 --> 00:32:46,120
Mm.

438
00:32:47,040 --> 00:32:47,880
Have you been waiting long?

439
00:32:49,040 --> 00:32:50,600
Why don't you go inside
and talk at home?

440
00:33:07,720 --> 00:33:09,640
Seriously, what's going on?

441
00:33:10,080 --> 00:33:10,640
Well...

442
00:33:10,800 --> 00:33:12,320
I really don't understand any of this.

443
00:33:19,440 --> 00:33:20,640
I'm moving out of the condo.

444
00:33:23,200 --> 00:33:24,360
If you want to keep living there,

445
00:33:25,120 --> 00:33:25,920
you can stay.

446
00:33:28,640 --> 00:33:29,720
Why are you moving out?

447
00:33:33,080 --> 00:33:34,560
What do you mean by moving out?
I mean...

448
00:33:35,800 --> 00:33:37,160
You don't want us
to live together anymore?

449
00:33:40,560 --> 00:33:41,120
Hey.

450
00:33:41,880 --> 00:33:45,160
If I did something wrong, just tell me.
Doing this doesn't solve anything.

451
00:33:49,920 --> 00:33:50,640
I want to break up.

452
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:53,560
Wayu.

453
00:33:55,400 --> 00:33:56,120
Let's break up.

454
00:33:59,880 --> 00:34:00,680
Your reason?

455
00:34:05,240 --> 00:34:06,120
I'm an adult now.

456
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:09,160
I'm not right for you, Wayu.

457
00:34:11,520 --> 00:34:12,960
You deserve someone
who can take care of you

458
00:34:14,240 --> 00:34:15,880
and understand you better than I can.

459
00:34:25,360 --> 00:34:26,280
Are you messing with me?

460
00:34:30,600 --> 00:34:32,200
Is there a hidden camera
somewhere, or...

461
00:34:33,480 --> 00:34:34,800
Is this some kind of show?

462
00:34:35,440 --> 00:34:37,760
If you just tell me,
I won't be mad at you, Krit.

463
00:34:38,440 --> 00:34:39,760
There's nothing like that, Wayu.

464
00:34:44,920 --> 00:34:46,000
I just finally realized...

465
00:34:48,880 --> 00:34:50,040
I don't love you that much.

466
00:34:53,240 --> 00:34:54,960
I want to focus on other things in life.

467
00:34:55,840 --> 00:34:57,480
I want to be the man
my dad wants me to be.

468
00:35:01,040 --> 00:35:02,040
I should marry Rose.

469
00:35:07,560 --> 00:35:08,200
You said...

470
00:35:10,400 --> 00:35:11,720
you wouldn't give up on us.

471
00:35:15,760 --> 00:35:16,480
You said...

472
00:35:17,400 --> 00:35:19,720
our story wouldn't end
like your past relationships.

473
00:35:22,080 --> 00:35:23,960
It was just a childish fling.
A passing phase.

474
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:29,400
I'm not a kid anymore.
I can't hold on to those ideals.

475
00:35:32,640 --> 00:35:33,640
Thank you for everything.

476
00:35:38,480 --> 00:35:39,080
Krit.

477
00:35:46,760 --> 00:35:47,320
At least...

478
00:35:48,600 --> 00:35:49,920
Can you at least tell me the truth?

479
00:35:50,200 --> 00:35:51,280
Why are you doing this?

480
00:36:04,600 --> 00:36:05,600
Let's end this peacefully, Wayu.

481
00:36:07,480 --> 00:36:08,480
Don't make this harder than it is.

482
00:36:09,600 --> 00:36:10,560
No, Krit.

483
00:36:13,400 --> 00:36:13,960
Krit.

484
00:37:24,640 --> 00:37:26,280
Hey, Wayu.

485
00:37:27,800 --> 00:37:29,080
What's wrong? Why'd you come back?

486
00:37:29,680 --> 00:37:32,200
Well, well. Look who came back.
You little punk.

487
00:37:32,320 --> 00:37:34,960
- You left your own mom in jail.
- Mom.

488
00:37:35,120 --> 00:37:36,400
I don't know what's wrong with him.

489
00:37:40,920 --> 00:37:41,560
Oops.

490
00:37:43,760 --> 00:37:45,360
Whatever it is, just let it out.

491
00:37:45,840 --> 00:37:48,240
Scream it out. Don't keep it
bottled up, dear.

492
00:37:48,800 --> 00:37:50,240
He doesn't want me anymore, Mom.

493
00:37:51,280 --> 00:37:54,320
So what if he doesn't?
Your mom and your sister are here.

494
00:37:54,640 --> 00:37:56,960
And you've got Singto too, right?

495
00:37:57,440 --> 00:37:58,760
You say that, but what about Captain?

496
00:38:14,280 --> 00:38:16,600
I never thought things
would work out, Mom.

497
00:38:18,840 --> 00:38:21,480
Nothing's gone the way I wanted.

498
00:38:24,720 --> 00:38:25,880
Just let it go.

499
00:38:26,400 --> 00:38:28,880
It's okay. When we get hurt,
we start over.

500
00:38:29,800 --> 00:38:31,360
No matter who does what,

501
00:38:31,960 --> 00:38:33,120
just come back home.

502
00:38:34,160 --> 00:38:38,400
If you don't want to work anymore,
you don't have to.

503
00:38:39,760 --> 00:38:41,280
I've already talked to Wai.

504
00:38:42,280 --> 00:38:44,040
I'll get treatment for my gambling.

505
00:38:47,480 --> 00:38:48,720
So you can finally rest.

506
00:39:01,040 --> 00:39:02,160
I'm sorry, Mom.

507
00:39:03,080 --> 00:39:04,080
Mm.

508
00:39:04,680 --> 00:39:05,600
Mm.

509
00:39:06,520 --> 00:39:09,880
No need to apologize.

510
00:39:12,000 --> 00:39:12,560
Well...

511
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:16,000
If you hadn't left me to get locked up,

512
00:39:16,320 --> 00:39:19,400
I wouldn't have realized what I've done.

513
00:39:21,160 --> 00:39:21,960
Hmm?

514
00:39:23,880 --> 00:39:26,760
Let's just say I backed
the wrong person for you.

515
00:39:26,760 --> 00:39:27,520
Alright.

516
00:39:27,760 --> 00:39:28,320
Okay.

517
00:39:29,080 --> 00:39:29,720
Uh...

518
00:39:29,840 --> 00:39:32,320
- Don't cry. Want to go to sleep?
- Uh-huh.

519
00:39:32,760 --> 00:39:35,000
And if you want to rest, then rest.

520
00:39:35,360 --> 00:39:37,040
It's just you. I can definitely
provide for you.

521
00:39:38,040 --> 00:39:39,920
A boyfriend isn't
that necessary, really.

522
00:39:40,720 --> 00:39:41,400
Huh.

523
00:39:42,360 --> 00:39:43,560
- Right?
- Yes, dear.

524
00:39:44,000 --> 00:39:44,840
You can rest, dear.

525
00:39:54,840 --> 00:39:56,000
Just take a break.

526
00:39:58,320 --> 00:39:59,440
It's okay, dear. It's okay.

527
00:39:59,440 --> 00:40:00,720
It's fine.

528
00:40:01,960 --> 00:40:06,280
- Just us three and Singto. So cozy.
- Yeah.

529
00:40:06,440 --> 00:40:07,560
Hmm.

530
00:40:22,360 --> 00:40:23,760
Hey, Tai.

531
00:40:24,240 --> 00:40:25,000
Wayu.

532
00:40:25,520 --> 00:40:26,880
How much longer are you
going to blow off work?

533
00:40:27,320 --> 00:40:28,760
Foei sent me to drag you back already.

534
00:40:29,680 --> 00:40:32,280
Jeez, who let you up here?
(Watch on www,kisskh,la to support Admin)

535
00:40:33,480 --> 00:40:34,800
Your mom did.

536
00:40:35,080 --> 00:40:37,280
The moment she found out
I'm your friend from the bar,

537
00:40:37,280 --> 00:40:39,320
she practically thanked me
for taking care of you.

538
00:40:39,320 --> 00:40:41,880
She basically rolled out the red carpet
and told me to come wake you up.

539
00:40:42,080 --> 00:40:44,440
Go tell Foei I'm not coming in.
I'm taking a month off.

540
00:40:47,600 --> 00:40:48,080
Ouch.

541
00:40:49,040 --> 00:40:51,560
I know you're torn up over the breakup,

542
00:40:52,240 --> 00:40:53,920
but are you really going to ditch
the gym and the bar like this?

543
00:40:54,560 --> 00:40:56,160
Be so irresponsible?

544
00:40:58,320 --> 00:40:58,920
Hey.

545
00:40:59,960 --> 00:41:02,640
You of all people are saying that to me?

546
00:41:04,160 --> 00:41:04,800
Hey.

547
00:41:06,320 --> 00:41:10,640
Your heart's still with you.
It didn't die with him.

548
00:41:11,600 --> 00:41:13,440
I've given you enough time to grieve.

549
00:41:14,800 --> 00:41:16,400
So get up and go shower.

550
00:41:16,400 --> 00:41:17,160
Ouch.

551
00:41:17,200 --> 00:41:18,040
- Tai.
- Let's go.

552
00:41:18,040 --> 00:41:19,640
I'm not going. Ouch.

553
00:41:20,880 --> 00:41:24,200
I've only been crying
my eyes out for two days.

554
00:41:25,680 --> 00:41:27,120
Why are you crying, then?

555
00:41:30,800 --> 00:41:35,280
If I believed Krit had left me to marry Rose,
I wouldn't make a fuss at all.

556
00:41:36,520 --> 00:41:37,720
But I'm sure that

557
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:39,720
he's not telling me the real reason.

558
00:41:41,800 --> 00:41:43,240
Knowing this is actually helpful, right?

559
00:41:46,400 --> 00:41:48,240
Do I not have the right to know, Tai?

560
00:41:48,520 --> 00:41:51,680
Don't I have the right to know
why he chose to cut me out of his life?

561
00:41:53,720 --> 00:41:54,320
Hey.

562
00:41:56,040 --> 00:41:57,320
What if one day

563
00:41:58,160 --> 00:42:01,160
I suddenly block you,
and you can't reach me at all?

564
00:42:01,760 --> 00:42:02,680
How would you feel?

565
00:42:03,560 --> 00:42:04,360
Huh?

566
00:42:05,600 --> 00:42:07,600
Do you understand
that I can't move on, Tai?

567
00:42:09,680 --> 00:42:11,000
I mean, if you're going to move on,

568
00:42:11,840 --> 00:42:13,240
you should know the reason, right?

569
00:42:15,520 --> 00:42:16,920
Go ask then.

570
00:42:17,200 --> 00:42:18,000
So it's over.

571
00:42:22,520 --> 00:42:23,920
And how am I supposed to ask him?

572
00:42:25,040 --> 00:42:26,720
Huh? He's not answering my calls.

573
00:42:27,000 --> 00:42:29,120
He's not replying on Line.
I can't get hold of him at all.

574
00:42:31,280 --> 00:42:32,360
Then why were you going to ask Krit?

575
00:42:33,600 --> 00:42:34,760
I mean Rose.

576
00:42:44,640 --> 00:42:47,120
Nun, the next order is coconut cake.

577
00:42:58,760 --> 00:43:00,080
No way.

578
00:43:00,080 --> 00:43:01,440
How could we possibly get married?

579
00:43:01,800 --> 00:43:04,520
Wayu knows I'm only
dating Krit as a cover.

580
00:43:08,000 --> 00:43:09,440
I feel the same way as Rose.

581
00:43:13,160 --> 00:43:14,120
So I don't understand

582
00:43:14,920 --> 00:43:16,480
why Krit had to lie to me.

583
00:43:19,040 --> 00:43:20,320
And then break up with me like that.

584
00:43:22,720 --> 00:43:24,360
Rose, do you have any idea?

585
00:43:27,800 --> 00:43:29,960
I don't know what happened either.

586
00:43:31,160 --> 00:43:34,480
But I do want to say something
to put you at ease, Wayu.

587
00:43:35,960 --> 00:43:38,000
The marriage Krit mentioned

588
00:43:38,160 --> 00:43:40,520
is absolutely impossible.
A million percent.

589
00:43:41,600 --> 00:43:42,920
I know my friend well.

590
00:43:43,800 --> 00:43:45,240
If it wasn't real,

591
00:43:45,600 --> 00:43:46,960
he never would've started it
in the first place.

592
00:43:49,840 --> 00:43:51,560
He hasn't fallen out of love
with you, Wayu.

593
00:43:53,640 --> 00:43:54,360
This whole thing...

594
00:43:54,960 --> 00:43:55,600
Uh...

595
00:43:56,400 --> 00:43:58,680
Could it be because of Krit's dad?

596
00:44:00,280 --> 00:44:03,560
His dad simply couldn't understand it,

597
00:44:03,840 --> 00:44:05,120
nor could he ever accept it.

598
00:44:06,280 --> 00:44:08,640
Then he should've
just said so honestly, right?

599
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:11,360
He made the call, broke up,
and gave the stuff back.

600
00:44:11,920 --> 00:44:13,040
What is this,
some kind of drama hero act?

601
00:44:13,680 --> 00:44:15,360
Like my friend's just some tissue,

602
00:44:15,560 --> 00:44:17,040
he can toss aside whenever he wants.

603
00:44:28,600 --> 00:44:29,320
Well...

604
00:44:30,240 --> 00:44:31,720
I'm really grateful to you, Rose.

605
00:44:33,920 --> 00:44:34,760
At least,

606
00:44:35,520 --> 00:44:36,720
now I know

607
00:44:37,440 --> 00:44:38,520
I was right.

608
00:44:40,840 --> 00:44:42,640
Krit chose to lie to me

609
00:44:44,080 --> 00:44:45,560
instead of telling me the truth.

610
00:44:48,240 --> 00:44:48,840
Well...

611
00:44:49,600 --> 00:44:51,800
He couldn't go against his family.

612
00:44:53,600 --> 00:44:55,000
Wayu, don't be mad at him.

613
00:45:00,080 --> 00:45:01,040
I'm not mad.

614
00:45:05,840 --> 00:45:07,000
I just want to know the truth.

615
00:45:15,320 --> 00:45:16,160
I'm leaving.

616
00:45:17,240 --> 00:45:18,520
Krit in your care.

617
00:45:20,440 --> 00:45:21,680
Why would you say that?

618
00:45:22,040 --> 00:45:23,160
That sounds like a bad omen.

619
00:45:24,040 --> 00:45:26,160
You should be the one
taking care of your boyfriend.

620
00:45:26,600 --> 00:45:27,160
Right?

621
00:45:28,760 --> 00:45:29,840
Let you do it, Rose.

622
00:45:30,960 --> 00:45:31,560
I think

623
00:45:32,360 --> 00:45:34,800
that I'm probably too young,
just like he said.

624
00:45:36,040 --> 00:45:36,920
And...

625
00:45:38,480 --> 00:45:40,200
I respect his decision.

626
00:45:41,680 --> 00:45:42,440
Goodbye.

627
00:45:45,200 --> 00:45:46,120
Goodbye.

628
00:45:53,360 --> 00:45:54,080
Sigh.

629
00:46:02,200 --> 00:46:04,240
Krit, have you eaten yet, dear?

630
00:46:04,520 --> 00:46:06,160
I made your favorite dish.

631
00:46:08,200 --> 00:46:08,920
I've already eaten.

632
00:46:21,560 --> 00:46:23,120
I broke up with Wayu,
just like you told me to.

633
00:46:24,760 --> 00:46:26,520
And I hope you'll keep away from him,

634
00:46:26,600 --> 00:46:28,040
like you promised.

635
00:46:31,960 --> 00:46:34,120
And Rose isn't marrying me anymore.

636
00:46:34,440 --> 00:46:35,520
Are you satisfied now?

637
00:46:37,000 --> 00:46:38,120
You don't need to worry.

638
00:46:38,800 --> 00:46:40,640
I've already arranged for you
to meet Mint Pimsawat,

639
00:46:40,800 --> 00:46:43,120
the minister's daughter.

640
00:46:43,680 --> 00:46:45,840
Next week, go get to know her.

641
00:46:46,720 --> 00:46:47,600
Whatever you want.

642
00:48:09,560 --> 00:48:10,520
(Sorry,)

643
00:48:10,760 --> 00:48:11,880
(I've got kind of a lot of stuff.)

644
00:48:12,480 --> 00:48:13,680
Then if you brought everything over...

645
00:48:14,120 --> 00:48:16,520
I'd probably have to buy another room
just for your clothes.

646
00:48:16,520 --> 00:48:17,600
Come on,

647
00:48:17,920 --> 00:48:18,960
that's an exaggeration.

648
00:48:19,480 --> 00:48:20,880
(It's not that bad, is it?)

649
00:48:24,080 --> 00:48:25,160
(I'm serious.)

650
00:48:26,840 --> 00:48:28,280
(If our relationship
gets to a certain point,)

651
00:48:29,920 --> 00:48:30,840
(I want to buy a house.)

652
00:48:32,040 --> 00:48:33,640
(I just want to keep
being with you on and on.)

653
00:48:34,080 --> 00:48:35,360
(Until)

654
00:48:35,560 --> 00:48:37,160
(we're sitting there plucking
each other's gray hairs.)

655
00:48:37,160 --> 00:48:43,320
♪Please lead me out of
the walls around my heart♪

656
00:48:43,320 --> 00:48:49,160
♪Please let me know
that you are my last♪

657
00:48:49,160 --> 00:48:55,960
♪Please wash away
all the tears from my past♪

658
00:48:55,960 --> 00:49:01,120
♪And fade them from my mind♪

659
00:49:01,120 --> 00:49:07,160
♪Please change the life
of this hopeless soul♪

660
00:49:07,160 --> 00:49:13,600
♪Please make today a reality,
not a dream♪

661
00:49:13,600 --> 00:49:19,880
♪Please let this love
belong to only you and me♪

662
00:49:19,880 --> 00:49:23,280
♪From now, from now♪

663
00:49:23,280 --> 00:49:27,880
♪Until our very last day♪

664
00:49:39,160 --> 00:49:42,160
(I've returned all of your things.)

665
00:49:43,200 --> 00:49:46,160
(If you don't want them,
you can just throw them away.)

666
00:49:48,880 --> 00:49:52,320
♪Into a beautiful light♪

667
00:50:28,160 --> 00:50:34,120
♪Please change the life
of this hopeless soul♪

668
00:50:34,120 --> 00:50:40,480
♪Please make today a reality,
not a dream♪

669
00:50:40,480 --> 00:50:46,960
♪Please let this love
belong to only you and me♪

670
00:50:46,960 --> 00:50:50,240
♪From now, from now♪

671
00:50:50,240 --> 00:50:55,440
♪Until our very last day♪

672
00:51:08,720 --> 00:51:11,640
He's serious this time, Krit.
There's no turning back now.

673
00:51:14,000 --> 00:51:19,880
♪Please lead me out of
the walls around my heart♪

674
00:51:19,880 --> 00:51:25,720
♪Please let me know
that you are my last♪

675
00:51:25,720 --> 00:51:29,240
He said if you don't come get it,
I can just throw it away.

676
00:51:29,520 --> 00:51:30,920
He won't keep them anymore.

677
00:51:32,720 --> 00:51:38,120
♪And fade them from my mind♪

678
00:52:08,800 --> 00:52:10,000
Whoa, bro. What's wrong?

679
00:52:11,240 --> 00:52:12,080
What happened?

680
00:52:12,960 --> 00:52:14,040
Are you allergic to shrimp?

681
00:52:16,800 --> 00:52:17,840
I'm not allergic to shrimp.

682
00:52:18,480 --> 00:52:20,160
Whatever it is, just leave him alone.

683
00:52:20,760 --> 00:52:22,120
Even if he is allergic to shrimp,

684
00:52:22,920 --> 00:52:24,800
he still looks better than all of us.

685
00:52:26,880 --> 00:52:27,440
Hey.

686
00:52:28,320 --> 00:52:30,240
I'm not that fragile, you know?

687
00:52:32,880 --> 00:52:34,400
So, did you work things out with him?

688
00:52:36,200 --> 00:52:36,760
Well...

689
00:52:37,600 --> 00:52:39,080
Yeah, I guess so.

690
00:52:40,560 --> 00:52:42,120
Forget it.

691
00:52:44,320 --> 00:52:45,320
Like I said,

692
00:52:45,920 --> 00:52:47,040
it doesn't matter anymore.

693
00:52:47,920 --> 00:52:49,400
What matters now is

694
00:52:50,000 --> 00:52:52,120
that I need to start focusing
on my own life again.

695
00:52:52,880 --> 00:52:53,960
Darn.

696
00:52:54,480 --> 00:52:55,960
When you decide to be strong,
you really are.

697
00:52:57,040 --> 00:52:59,240
That's why you're my best friend.

698
00:52:59,920 --> 00:53:01,560
So, what do you want to eat?

699
00:53:01,760 --> 00:53:02,760
I'll treat you.

700
00:53:03,360 --> 00:53:04,160
Come on, want anything?

701
00:53:04,720 --> 00:53:05,600
I'll order it for you.

702
00:53:07,200 --> 00:53:08,680
No, I can't eat.

703
00:53:09,920 --> 00:53:11,160
Hey, you've got to eat.

704
00:53:12,000 --> 00:53:13,880
If you go to work on an empty stomach,

705
00:53:14,800 --> 00:53:16,200
you're definitely going to pass out.

706
00:53:16,800 --> 00:53:17,680
How about this one?

707
00:53:18,200 --> 00:53:18,960
I'll order

708
00:53:19,240 --> 00:53:20,280
Tom Yum Fried Rice.

709
00:53:20,360 --> 00:53:21,360
It's your favorite, right?

710
00:53:21,960 --> 00:53:23,440
Want it?

711
00:53:23,520 --> 00:53:25,440
Wait here. I'll go order it
for you, buddy.

712
00:53:25,440 --> 00:53:26,680
Sigh.

713
00:53:31,640 --> 00:53:32,400
Hey, bro.

714
00:53:33,200 --> 00:53:34,960
I don't know what you're going through.

715
00:53:35,800 --> 00:53:37,200
But it'll pass.

716
00:53:38,360 --> 00:53:39,640
No matter what happens,

717
00:53:40,040 --> 00:53:41,200
don't give up.

718
00:53:50,280 --> 00:53:51,280
Hey, Sky.

719
00:53:51,720 --> 00:53:52,800
Look at Wayu.

720
00:53:53,400 --> 00:53:54,320
I don't know what's wrong with him.

721
00:53:55,240 --> 00:53:56,120
What should we do?

722
00:53:58,000 --> 00:53:58,760
This one?

723
00:53:59,760 --> 00:54:00,480
Okay.

724
00:54:03,240 --> 00:54:04,720
Snacks from Sky.

725
00:54:05,320 --> 00:54:06,440
Hang in there.

726
00:54:33,840 --> 00:54:34,560
Foei.

727
00:54:36,440 --> 00:54:38,320
I need to tell you something
after the show.

728
00:54:42,360 --> 00:54:44,160
I think I know what you're going to say.

729
00:54:45,920 --> 00:54:47,440
Once this week's over,

730
00:54:48,720 --> 00:54:50,240
I'd like to quit.

731
00:54:50,720 --> 00:54:52,840
Hmm.

732
00:54:52,840 --> 00:54:55,760
I've put my own life
on hold for too long.

733
00:54:57,840 --> 00:54:59,840
If it's been that long,
and you still want to leave,

734
00:55:00,600 --> 00:55:02,640
then I believe you've really
thought it through.

735
00:55:06,200 --> 00:55:08,040
But you have to support
your own education.

736
00:55:08,680 --> 00:55:10,360
Can you really afford food, travel,

737
00:55:10,720 --> 00:55:11,800
and tuition?

738
00:55:12,480 --> 00:55:14,120
On top of that, you might even have to
clear your mom's debts too.

739
00:55:19,080 --> 00:55:21,280
Actually, I do have some savings.

740
00:55:21,840 --> 00:55:23,480
And my sister's been
helping out lately too.

741
00:55:24,400 --> 00:55:27,240
So my plan is to study

742
00:55:27,560 --> 00:55:29,040
and work part-time too.

743
00:55:30,880 --> 00:55:31,600
Whew.

744
00:55:32,440 --> 00:55:33,120
Okay.

745
00:55:33,800 --> 00:55:35,000
Don't worry about that.

746
00:55:35,640 --> 00:55:36,920
I'll sponsor your tuition myself.

747
00:55:37,640 --> 00:55:38,320
What?

748
00:55:38,800 --> 00:55:39,840
Are you serious?

749
00:55:42,320 --> 00:55:44,360
But that's a lot of money, Foei.

750
00:55:46,400 --> 00:55:49,600
Yeah. I just want to support
someone as determined as you.

751
00:55:50,040 --> 00:55:52,360
Just promise me you'll finish school,

752
00:55:53,040 --> 00:55:55,280
and make your dream come true.

753
00:55:58,160 --> 00:55:59,520
Thank you, Foei.

754
00:56:01,240 --> 00:56:03,040
But really, you don't have to.

755
00:56:05,000 --> 00:56:08,480
Without you, I would've been done
for a long time ago.

756
00:56:09,760 --> 00:56:12,480
Especially now, I feel even worse
about Moonlit.

757
00:56:14,840 --> 00:56:16,280
Why overthink it?

758
00:56:17,160 --> 00:56:19,040
Just think of it
as a scholarship from us.

759
00:56:19,920 --> 00:56:21,040
Once you graduate,

760
00:56:21,920 --> 00:56:24,160
you can come back
and renovate the place for free.

761
00:56:24,320 --> 00:56:26,640
By then, I'll get
my investment back in full.

762
00:56:29,920 --> 00:56:30,960
Go give it your all.

763
00:56:32,080 --> 00:56:33,000
You know.

764
00:56:33,440 --> 00:56:34,480
Titles don't last.

765
00:56:35,320 --> 00:56:37,120
Legends do.

766
00:56:56,040 --> 00:56:59,040
♪Am I too ugly to get a chance?♪

767
00:56:59,680 --> 00:57:02,440
♪If I want to lock you down as my girl?♪

